name: Lt. Governor Kevin Meyer
tweet: This holiday season I would like to remind everyone to make safe choices and never drive under the influence. Keep yourself and other drivers safe by designating a sober driver or taking public transportation. #DriveSober  https://t.co/Rr2UzUBnym

name: Lt. Governor Kevin Meyer

name: Lt. Governor Kevin Meyer
tweet: In Alaska, the Lt. Governor oversees the Division of Elections. If you have questions about the election process or voter information, reach out to our team. Follow our election officials @ak_elections – they are Alaska’s trusted source on voting & elections. #TrustedInfo2020

name: Lt. Governor Kevin Meyer
tweet: Happy Veterans Day to all of the brave men and women who have served and currently serve in the United States Armed Forces. Without the sacrifices these honorable soldiers have made we would not be the country we are today.  https://t.co/Kf2dsGCgRY

name: Lt. Governor Kevin Meyer
tweet: It was a privilege to attend the Department of Corrections Academy graduation ceremony yesterday with Commissioner Dahlstrom. Congratulations to all of the graduates! Thank you for your dedication to making our state a safer place.  https://t.co/OfeMTnQsjJ

name: Lt. Governor Kevin Meyer
tweet: Happy Halloween! name: Lt. Governor Kevin Meyer
tweet: Did you know that October is Careers in Construction Month? Construction offers many reliable life-long careers that benefit Alaska’s workforce, economy and development. It is important to educate our future generations about the opportunities careers in construction can provide.

name: Lt. Governor Kevin Meyer
tweet: Happy Alaska Day! Today we celebrate the 152nd anniversary of the official transfer of the Territory of Alaska from Russia to the United States. We are all lucky to call such a beautiful and diverse place our home. I hope all Alaskans have a great day of celebrating our state.  https://t.co/4JhZRKNHhV

name: Lt. Governor Kevin Meyer
tweet: As technology becomes more advanced so do cybercriminals. It is important to take simple but effective security measures such as regularly changing & creating strong passwords and updating your privacy settings. #BeCyberSmart and #CyberAware

name: Lt. Governor Kevin Meyer
tweet: Today is #WorldMentalHealthDay. The focus this year is close to our hearts here in Alaska, suicide prevention. Alaska has one of the highest suicide rates in the country. Remember that it is important to take care of your mental health and be there for others who may need you.  https://t.co/S5UzJ5ecYt

name: Lt. Governor Kevin Meyer

tweet: October is National Cybersecurity Awareness Month. Cybersecurity is growing more and more important as technology continues to advance. During NCSAM you can follow @staysafeonline and @cyber to stay updated on how you can #BeCyberSmart and #CyberAware.
